title: Serrated Thumb Forceps 5.5″
description:
The Serrated Thumb Forceps 5.5″ are versatile surgical instruments designed to securely grasp and handle tissues, dressings, or other materials during medical, dental, and veterinary procedures. The serrated tips provide a non-slip grip, ensuring delicate handling without tissue damage. With an ergonomic design, these forceps allow for precise control, making them a preferred tool for clinicians.

Crafted from high-quality stainless steel, these forceps offer exceptional durability, corrosion resistance, and compatibility with frequent sterilization cycles, ensuring reliability over time.

title: Castroviejo 15cm
description: The principal use for Castroviejo needle holders is microsurgery. The delicacy of their tip and the handle’s mechanism, which enables the jaws to be opened with little effort, set them apart from other needle holders.

title: Carmalt Forceps
description:
The Carmalt Forceps are robust, hemostatic surgical instruments commonly used to clamp large blood vessels, tissues, or pedicles during surgical procedures. They feature longitudinal serrations along the jaws with cross-serrations at the tip, ensuring a secure grip on tissues and preventing slippage. These forceps are ideal for surgeries requiring reliable control over large structures, such as in general, veterinary, or obstetric surgeries.

Manufactured from high-grade stainless steel, these forceps are designed for durability, corrosion resistance, and ease of cleaning. Their ergonomic design ensures a comfortable grip for precise handling during procedures.

title: DeBakey Atraumatic Tissue Forceps 16cm
description:
The DeBakey Atraumatic Tissue Forceps is a high-precision surgical tool made from premium stainless steel, ensuring durability, corrosion resistance, and compatibility with frequent sterilization, including autoclaving. Designed with fine serrated jaws, it enables secure grasping of delicate tissues with minimal trauma, making it ideal for cardiovascular, gastrointestinal, and general surgeries. These forceps offer exceptional control for handling vessels and soft tissues without causing crushing injuries.

Its lightweight construction and ergonomic design reduce hand fatigue during prolonged use. The stainless steel material ensures long-lasting reliability, maintaining sterility and functionality even after numerous sterilization cycles

title: Mathieu Foreign Body Forceps
description: General and urology surgeons utilize the Mathieu Foreign Body Forceps, a specialist tool, to grip, hold, and remove foreign bodies and other surgical materials from the operating site. Relatively small Alligator Jaws for the Best Grip.

title: Sponge Forceps 17cm
description:
Surgical Holdings’ sponge holding forceps are meant to grip and hold sponges and/or swabs while performing a medical treatment or surgery. Many different sorts of medical procedures and surgeries require sponge holding forceps.

Made of Japanese Steel 410

title: Mayo-Bakes Gall Stone Forceps Curved
description: General and gastrointestinal surgeons employ the Mayo-Bakes Gall Stone Forceps to grip, statically hold, and move biliary calculus out of the bile ducts. Curved Profiles for a Variety of Uses Self-Retaining Clamping with a Ratchet System. Finger Rings with Ergonomic Design for Better Handling

title: Millin Capsule Grasping Forceps 22cm
description: The Millin Capsule Grasping Forceps is a specialised device used by urologists to grip, hold, and manipulate soft tissues during a variety of urogenital surgery operations. Jaws with a side angle for better surgical reach.

title: Spring Scissor 15cm
description: Frequently, iridectomy and corneal procedures employ Castroviejo scissors. Their delicate and distinctive design, created by our skilled makers, features fine, sharp tips and a double leaf mechanism that enable the precise and efficient cutting of tiny tissue and sutures.

title: Goldman Fox Scissors Straight 5″
description: Goldman Fox Scissor Supercut straight made with high quality stainless steel for maximum hardness.

title: Plastic Handle Bandage Scissors 14cm
description: Bandage scissors, also known as bandage forceps, makes it simpler to cut bandages without cutting into the skin.

title: Wertheim Gynecological Scissor
description: The Wertheim Gynecological Scissor is a flexible tool for cutting soft/dense tissue and blunt dissection during surgery. To Improve Deep Tissue Access, The Working End Is Curved. Long Shanks Give You More Control During Surgery to Minimize Trauma To Surrounding Tissue, Use These Blunt/Blunt Tips.

title: Wagner Dissecting Scissor 12cm
description: The Wagner Dissecting Scissor is a multipurpose scissor that is used for precise tissue dissection. Surgical surgeons utilise it to accomplish sharp dissection and tissue cutting in cardiovascular and general procedures. Dissection is made easier with bevelled blades. User Fatigue Can Be Reduced By Using Lightweight Materials. For Better Control, Ergonomic Ring Handles

title: Thorek Dissecting Scissors 18.5cm
description: The Thorek Dissecting Scissor is a flexible tool for dissecting soft tissues bluntly. It’s usually utilised for abdominal hysterectomies, but it can also be used for a variety of other gynaecological and general procedures. Long Shanks For Better Deep Tissue Access Short Blade to Shank Ratio for Better Dissection Control Curved Blades Make Manipulation Easier

title: Standard Surgical Scissors BL/BL,Curved
description: Sharp Operating Scissors shred tougher tissue and are generally used for dissection, whereas dull Surgical Scissors are more commonly used for cutting sutures, tubing, or gauze.

title: Standard SH/SH Straight
description: Sharp Operating Scissors shred tougher tissue and are generally used for dissection, whereas dull Surgical Scissors are more commonly used for cutting sutures, tubing, or gauze.

title: Standard SH/BL Straight Operating Scissors
description: Sharp Operating Scissors shred tougher tissue and are generally used for dissection, whereas dull Surgical Scissors are more commonly used for cutting sutures, tubing, or gauze

title: Finochietto Rib Retractor (Lateral blades 15 mm spreading 75 mm)
description: The Finochietto Rib Spreader is a specialized surgical instrument designed to provide access to internal organs during thoracotomy procedures. It is widely used in cardiothoracic and trauma operations, ensuring precision and efficiency in critical surgical settings.

title: Young Prostatic Retractor 22cm
description: The Young Prostatic Retractor is a specialised device used by urology surgeons to pull back and hold the muscular tissues around the prostate, as well as the prostate itself, in order to get a better view of the surgical site

title: Volkmann Retractor 22cm
description: The Volkmann Retractor is a prominent hand-held equipment that surgeons use to manipulate tissues during distal limb procedures, particularly those involving tiny joints, soles, and palms. Grasps little or large slices of tissue with one to six prongs. Prongs that are sharp to prevent injury to nearby structures. Hollow Ringed Handle With Ergonomic Ergonomic Ergonomic Ergonomic Ergonomic Ergonomic Ergonomic Ergon

title: Rose Tracheal Retractor
description: In tracheotomy procedures, the Rose Tracheal Retractor helps otolaryngologists remove neck tissues. It aids in dislodging the cricoid cartilage and pretracheal tissues, allowing for a better view of the tracheal incision. To provide non-slip grips, the handle is flat. For a clear field of vision, a slim shaft is used. For Safe Manipulation, Use Blunt Blades.

title: O’Conner Skin Hook 16cm
description: The O’Conner Skin Hook is a multifunctional surgical device that can be used to retract soft tissue, elevate skin flaps, or simply isolate biopsy samples during harvesting procedures by professionals in many fields. To Achieve Optimal Retractions, Use a Sharp-Pointed Tip. Deep Surgical Reach is facilitated by the tapered shaft. Ergonomic. Maximum control is ensured by a solid handle.

title: Middeldorf Retractor
description: During plastic and maxillofacial procedures, the Middeldorf Retractor is a flexible surgical instrument that allows surgeons to mobilise, retract, and lay tissues aside. The tissues usually treated are delicate structures in the oral cavity, such as mucoperiosteal flaps, cheeks, lips, and tongue. Fenestrated Traumatic Blade For Maximum Exposure Retracting Small & Large Blades in a Variety of Sizes

title: Guthrie Skin Retractor
description: Plastic surgeons can use the Guthrie Skin Retractor to grab and mobilise soft tissues, exposing small anatomical areas without harming the dermis. For optimum skin retraction, sharp double prongs are used. Surgical Manipulation Made Easier With An Elongated Flat Handle To Reduce Unwanted Trauma, different hook widths are available.
